#: LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:64
msgid ""
"If this button is visible, there are breakpoints that you tried to set, but "
"that the debugger refused. This most often happens when the breakpoint is "
"inside a library that hadn't been loaded when the debugger started.\n"
"\n"
"Click to offer the breakpoints to the debugger again."
