#: LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:121
msgid "Select the type of the breakpoint:"
msgstr ""

#: LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:138
msgid "Break by line, function or memory address:"
msgstr ""

#: LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:154
msgid "Line number"
msgstr ""

#: LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:162
msgid ""
"Enter the line-number on which you wish to break. It's assumed to refer to "
"the current file: if it doesn't, please enter the correct filepath below."
msgstr ""

#: LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:179
msgid ""
"If you wish to break when a particular function is entered, insert its name "
"here. In C just the name will do e.g. 'main' or 'myFoo'. For C++ class "
"methods, you need to do 'MyClass::myFoo'\n"
"\n"
"Alternatively you can enter a regular expression, and tick the checkbox "
"below. A breakpoint will then be set on all matching functions."
msgstr ""

#: LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:190
msgid "This is a regex"
msgstr ""

#: LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:193
msgid ""
"If you wish to insert a breakpoint on several functions, you can tick this "
"box, then enter a suitable regular expression in the textctrl above."
msgstr ""

#: LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:198
msgid "Memory address:"
msgstr ""

#: LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:207
msgid ""
"To break on a memory address, enter the address here.\n"
"e.g. 0x0a1b2c3d or 12345678"
msgstr ""

#: LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:215
msgid "In file:"
msgstr ""

#: LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:226
msgid ""
"If you've entered a line-number, its assumed to refer to the current file. "
"If it isn't, enter the correct filename here.\n"
"\n"
"For a function, a file is usually not required. However, if you have several "
"functions with the same name, in several different files (do people _really_ "
"do that?) and you want to break on only one of those, enter the correct "
"filename here."
msgstr ""

